  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth version`\r\nOS & Version: OSX\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nIPC peer\r\n```\r\ngeth --ipcpath ~/Library/Ethereum/geth1.ipc --datadir \"./privatechain3\" --networkid 1234 --port=\"33333\" console\r\n```\r\n\r\nRPC peer\r\n\r\n```\r\ngeth  --ipcdisable --rpc --rpcport 8103 --datadir \"./privatechain/02\" --networkid 123 --rpcapi=\"db,eth,net,web3,personal\" --nodiscover  --port=30308 --rpccorsdomain=\"*\"  console \r\n```\r\n\r\nthey both init by the same genesis.json\r\n\r\nbut IPC peer connect to IPC peers and  RPC peer to RPC peer all good.Why no RPC to IPC?\r\n\r\nAnother question is https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/Setting-up-private-network-or-local-cluster\r\n\r\nit says\r\n\r\n>the ipc endpoint is unique or the ipc interface is disabled\r\n\r\nWhy it says that?Beacuse I can connect both IPC peer with the same IPC endpoint.",
