    "body": "> the ipc endpoint is unique or the ipc interface is disabled\r\n\r\nOn unix/osx geth uses unix sockets and on Windows named pipes. These sockets/pipes need to be unique for the same reason you cannot save 2 different files with the same filename in the same directory.\r\n\r\nProbably your private network nodes find other nodes through the default bootnodes. This is not a problem. Your nodes won't sync with any of these other nodes. If you set up a multi node private network I recommend setting up a a custom bootnode so you don't have to manually add peers.\r\n\r\n",
