    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> But if the bootnode shutdown and we didn't notice will new add peer not able to join the network?\r\n\r\nIf the node has never connected to the network before it will not know of any peers except for the bootnodes you specify, so if those are down it will not be able to join the network. For fault tolerance you can have several bootnodes running in different locations and feed the full list of bootnodes to the new nodes you start (which is what the public network does, those bootnodes being hardcoded in the client)\r\n\r\n> Is ethereum using UDP broadcast or multicast ?\r\n\r\nThe discovery protocol uses UDP.  Make sure the bootnodes are reachable over the network.",
